intent:
  id: intent/2026-05-02/scratchpad-thread-id-squatting#b14a24d8fadf
  change_type: fix
  scope: scratchpad
  summary: Prevent explicit scratchpad ids from reserving another thread's default id.
  decision: Reject open_scratchpad calls that pass an explicit scratchpad_id which parses as a ThreadId and differs from the current runtime thread id, so a child spawned by one session cannot create or open a scratchpad as another session's default thread id.
  constraints:
    - A thread must not create a new scratchpad file named after another thread id before that other thread creates its default pad.
    - A child launched by Session A must not become or reserve Session B's scratchpad, even when Session B is idle.
    - Existing Session B scratchpads must remain reopenable by Session B and unchanged after a rejected Session A child attempt.
    - Ordinary non-UUID custom scratchpad ids remain allowed; UUID-shaped custom ids are reserved for real thread ids.
  intent_priority: must
  code_locations:
    - codex-rs/core/src/tools/handlers/builtin_scratchpad.rs::open_scratchpad
    - codex-rs/core/src/tools/handlers/builtin_scratchpad.rs::open_scratchpad_rejects_explicit_other_thread_id_before_creation
    - codex-rs/core/src/tools/handlers/builtin_scratchpad.rs::open_scratchpad_cannot_launch_child_as_existing_session_owner
